Stills From Last Night
Franticness and mundanities of real life only allow for a nightly window for finding the slower pace and the right seclusion for plunging into the screen's light, into programming code and generating images. I resigned myself to the fact that sleep deprivation seemed the only way for me to sustain the creation process. These diapositives can be seen as a photographic documentary of the sites I'm passing through in a blur, under my artificial daylight.
